- リモートで環境構築してくれる、GitHub Codespacesをこのリポジトリで使ってみたのですが、初期インストールされているHugoは拡張版ではないためSCSSに対応しておらず、 `hugo` コマンドがエラーで使えませんでした
- DockerfileでHugo_extendedのバージョンを指定してインストールさせると解決するかも？ということで追加してみました！

node.title: Add debugging to user settings page
node.body:
It would be helpful to have an endpoint in PL that showed what data we received from the authentication provider. This wouldn't be an everyday requirement, but might help us quickly troubleshoot SSO setup with institution admins.

The User Settings page seemed like a reasonable place to display some additional authn information. This PR adds a "?debug" query flag to the page to enable embedding more information. There is a toggle for this mode at the bottom of the page -- if we want this functionality to be more hidden, we can remove the visible link to debug mode.

Right now it only shows LTI 1.3 authentication data from the session. That still needs to be saved there; either in this PR or a different one.

nodes.bodyText:
Prior art is our support of ?RelayState=test in the SAML flow:

  
    
      PrairieLearn/apps/prairielearn/src/ee/auth/saml/router.ts
    
    
         Line 74
      in
      e13764d
    
  
  
    

        
          
           if (req.body.RelayState === 'test') { 
        
    
  


If that query param is present, we render all the received attributes back to the user instead of authenticating them.
I don't know if OIDC has a similar bit of state that we can pass through the IdP, but if it does, it'd be nice to have the debug mode of both auth systems behave similarly.
From a few quick searches, I'm not sure how supported the concept of RelayState is with OIDC.
ChatGPT suggests that there's a state parameter that we can use to persist data through the IdP flow: https://chat.openai.com/share/009efb1e-20f5-4033-a126-d2491c5fa351
